Package: abimaQ
Title: Adaptive Bootstrap Inference for Quantile Mediation Analysis with
        Enhanced Statistical Power
Version: 1.0
Authors@R: 
    c(person("Canyi", "Chen", , "cychen.stats@outlook.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-0673-5812")),
           person("Yinqiu", "He", role = c("aut")),
           person("Huixia J.", "Wang", role = c("aut")),
           person("Gongjun", "Xu", role = c("aut")),
    person("Peter X.-K.", "Song", , role = c("aut", "cph")))
Description: Assess whether and how a specific continuous exposure affects the outcome of interest at a given quantile level through one-dimensional mediator using an  adaptive bootstrap (AB) approach. The AB method allows to make inference for composite null hypotheses of no mediation effect, providing valid type I error control and thus optimizes statistical power. For more technical details, refer to Chen, He, Wang, Xu and Song <doi:10.48550/arXiv.2412.15401>
